The paper proposes an approach to automatically learn API migration patterns from code examples to assist Android app developers with API migrations. This involves analyzing changes in API usage in code examples, which suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The approach also involves machine learning techniques to learn patterns, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). The evaluation involves migrating API calls in open source Android apps, which suggests a focus on software development (cs.SD). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques to identify relevant code examples, which suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR).
